ABC's formality and centralization? ABC Corp. is formalized and centralized. Formalization is how well an organization standardizes and documents its processes. ABC Corp. has well-documented processes and defined job descriptions for each employee. Since workers must follow a set of rules and processes, the organization is highly formalized. Centralization is the degree to which an organization's senior leaders make decisions. The CEO of ABC Corp. reports to a few supervisors, and low-level workers have minimal decision-making power. Since senior management makes decisions, the corporation is very centralized. 